{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":330,"text":"The kind of neuroscience that I do and my colleagues do"},{"time":3181,"text":"is almost like the weatherman."},{"time":5347,"text":"We are always chasing storms."},{"time":8863,"text":"We want to see and measure storms -- brainstorms, that is."},{"time":13746,"text":"And we all talk about brainstorms in our daily lives,"},{"time":16514,"text":"but we rarely see or listen to one."},{"time":19964,"text":"So I always like to start these talks"},{"time":21598,"text":"by actually introducing you to one of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24580,"text":"Actually, the first time we recorded more than one neuron --"},{"time":28007,"text":"a hundred brain cells simultaneously --"},{"time":30230,"text":"we could measure the electrical sparks"},{"time":32699,"text":"of a hundred cells in the same animal,"},{"time":35379,"text":"this is the first image we got,"},{"time":37181,"text":"the first 10 seconds of this recording."},{"time":39496,"text":"So we got a little snippet of a thought,"},{"time":42847,"text":"and we could see it in front of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45752,"text":"I always tell the students"},{"time":46764,"text":"that we could also call neuroscientists some sort of astronomer,"},{"time":50870,"text":"because we are dealing with a system"},{"time":52496,"text":"that is only comparable in terms of number of cells"},{"time":55413,"text":"to the number of galaxies that we have in the universe."},{"time":58349,"text":"And here we are, out of billions of neurons,"},{"time":61379,"text":"just recording, 10 years ago, a hundred."},{"time":64197,"text":"We are doing a thousand now."},{"time":65780,"text":"And we hope to understand something fundamental about our human nature."},{"time":71180,"text":"Because, if you don't know yet,"},{"time":73112,"text":"everything that we use to define what human nature is comes from these storms,"},{"time":78362,"text":"comes from these storms that roll over the hills and valleys of our brains"},{"time":83013,"text":"and define our memories, our beliefs,"},{"time":86898,"text":"our feelings, our plans for the future."},{"time":89598,"text":"Everything that we ever do,"},{"time":91996,"text":"everything that every human has ever done, do or will do,"},{"time":97063,"text":"requires the toil of populations of neurons producing these kinds of storms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102497,"text":"And the sound of a brainstorm, if you've never heard one,"},{"time":104980,"text":"is somewhat like this."},{"time":108329,"text":"You can put it louder if you can."},{"time":111475,"text":"My son calls this \"making popcorn while listening to a badly-tuned A.M. station.\""},{"time":117878,"text":"This is a brain."},{"time":119363,"text":"This is what happens when you route these electrical storms to a loudspeaker"},{"time":122797,"text":"and you listen to a hundred brain cells firing,"},{"time":125663,"text":"your brain will sound like this -- my brain, any brain."},{"time":130285,"text":"And what we want to do as neuroscientists in this time"},{"time":134047,"text":"is to actually listen to these symphonies, these brain symphonies,"},{"time":139397,"text":"and try to extract from them the messages they carry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142797,"text":"In particular, about 12 years ago"},{"time":145648,"text":"we created a preparation that we named brain-machine interfaces."},{"time":148696,"text":"And you have a scheme here that describes how it works."},{"time":151398,"text":"The idea is, let's have some sensors that listen to these storms, this electrical firing,"},{"time":156964,"text":"and see if you can, in the same time that it takes"},{"time":160046,"text":"for this storm to leave the brain and reach the legs or the arms of an animal --"},{"time":165015,"text":"about half a second --"},{"time":167879,"text":"let's see if we can read these signals,"},{"time":170230,"text":"extract the motor messages that are embedded in it,"},{"time":173630,"text":"translate it into digital commands"},{"time":175902,"text":"and send it to an artificial device"},{"time":177788,"text":"that will reproduce the voluntary motor wheel of that brain in real time."},{"time":183681,"text":"And see if we can measure how well we can translate that message"},{"time":187529,"text":"when we compare to the way the body does that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191047,"text":"And if we can actually provide feedback,"},{"time":193913,"text":"sensory signals that go back from this robotic, mechanical, computational actuator"},{"time":199647,"text":"that is now under the control of the brain,"},{"time":201898,"text":"back to the brain,"},{"time":203209,"text":"how the brain deals with that,"},{"time":205330,"text":"of receiving messages from an artificial piece of machinery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210231,"text":"And that's exactly what we did 10 years ago."},{"time":212552,"text":"We started with a superstar monkey called Aurora"},{"time":215513,"text":"that became one of the superstars of this field."},{"time":217981,"text":"And Aurora liked to play video games."},{"time":220280,"text":"As you can see here,"},{"time":221653,"text":"she likes to use a joystick, like any one of us, any of our kids, to play this game."},{"time":226597,"text":"And as a good primate, she even tries to cheat before she gets the right answer."},{"time":231268,"text":"So even before a target appears that she's supposed to cross"},{"time":235551,"text":"with the cursor that she's controlling with this joystick,"},{"time":238401,"text":"Aurora is trying to find the target, no matter where it is."},{"time":242352,"text":"And if she's doing that,"},{"time":243821,"text":"because every time she crosses that target with the little cursor,"},{"time":247135,"text":"she gets a drop of Brazilian orange juice."},{"time":250085,"text":"And I can tell you, any monkey will do anything for you"},{"time":253035,"text":"if you get a little drop of Brazilian orange juice."},{"time":256135,"text":"Actually any primate will do that."},{"time":258866,"text":"Think about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260200,"text":"Well, while Aurora was playing this game, as you saw,"},{"time":263600,"text":"and doing a thousand trials a day"},{"time":266035,"text":"and getting 97 percent correct and 350 milliliters of orange juice,"},{"time":269918,"text":"we are recording the brainstorms that are produced in her head"},{"time":273317,"text":"and sending them to a robotic arm"},{"time":274964,"text":"that was learning to reproduce the movements that Aurora was making."},{"time":278835,"text":"Because the idea was to actually turn on this brain-machine interface"},{"time":282618,"text":"and have Aurora play the game just by thinking,"},{"time":287318,"text":"without interference of her body."},{"time":289935,"text":"Her brainstorms would control an arm"},{"time":292851,"text":"that would move the cursor and cross the target."},{"time":295560,"text":"And to our shock, that's exactly what Aurora did."},{"time":298751,"text":"She played the game without moving her body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302951,"text":"So every trajectory that you see of the cursor now,"},{"time":305188,"text":"this is the exact first moment she got that."},{"time":308400,"text":"That's the exact first moment"},{"time":310184,"text":"a brain intention was liberated from the physical domains of a body of a primate"},{"time":316951,"text":"and could act outside, in that outside world,"},{"time":320651,"text":"just by controlling an artificial device."},{"time":323617,"text":"And Aurora kept playing the game, kept finding the little target"},{"time":328534,"text":"and getting the orange juice that she wanted to get, that she craved for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332451,"text":"Well, she did that because she, at that time, had acquired a new arm."},{"time":339152,"text":"The robotic arm that you see moving here 30 days later,"},{"time":342115,"text":"after the first video that I showed to you,"},{"time":344801,"text":"is under the control of Aurora's brain"},{"time":347451,"text":"and is moving the cursor to get to the target."},{"time":350619,"text":"And Aurora now knows that she can play the game with this robotic arm,"},{"time":354518,"text":"but she has not lost the ability to use her biological arms to do what she pleases."},{"time":360234,"text":"She can scratch her back, she can scratch one of us, she can play another game."},{"time":364301,"text":"By all purposes and means,"},{"time":365901,"text":"Aurora's brain has incorporated that artificial device"},{"time":370017,"text":"as an extension of her body."},{"time":372767,"text":"The model of the self that Aurora had in her mind"},{"time":376300,"text":"has been expanded to get one more arm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380384,"text":"Well, we did that 10 years ago."},{"time":382734,"text":"Just fast forward 10 years."},{"time":385567,"text":"Just last year we realized that you don't even need to have a robotic device."},{"time":390550,"text":"You can just build a computational body, an avatar, a monkey avatar."},{"time":396034,"text":"And you can actually use it for our monkeys to either interact with them,"},{"time":400284,"text":"or you can train them to assume in a virtual world"},{"time":404723,"text":"the first-person perspective of that avatar"},{"time":407767,"text":"and use her brain activity to control the movements of the avatar's arms or legs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413418,"text":"And what we did basically was to train the animals"},{"time":416184,"text":"to learn how to control these avatars"},{"time":419234,"text":"and explore objects that appear in the virtual world."},{"time":423133,"text":"And these objects are visually identical,"},{"time":425434,"text":"but when the avatar crosses the surface of these objects,"},{"time":429317,"text":"they send an electrical message that is proportional to the microtactile texture of the object"},{"time":435717,"text":"that goes back directly to the monkey's brain,"},{"time":439733,"text":"informing the brain what it is the avatar is touching."},{"time":444785,"text":"And in just four weeks, the brain learns to process this new sensation"},{"time":449550,"text":"and acquires a new sensory pathway -- like a new sense."},{"time":455984,"text":"And you truly liberate the brain now"},{"time":458400,"text":"because you are allowing the brain to send motor commands to move this avatar."},{"time":462784,"text":"And the feedback that comes from the avatar is being processed directly by the brain"},{"time":467784,"text":"without the interference of the skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470217,"text":"So what you see here is this is the design of the task."},{"time":472751,"text":"You're going to see an animal basically touching these three targets."},{"time":477001,"text":"And he has to select one because only one carries the reward,"},{"time":481350,"text":"the orange juice that they want to get."},{"time":483217,"text":"And he has to select it by touch using a virtual arm, an arm that doesn't exist."},{"time":488850,"text":"And that's exactly what they do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490850,"text":"This is a complete liberation of the brain"},{"time":494285,"text":"from the physical constraints of the body and the motor in a perceptual task."},{"time":498567,"text":"The animal is controlling the avatar to touch the targets."},{"time":502734,"text":"And he's sensing the texture by receiving an electrical message directly in the brain."},{"time":508385,"text":"And the brain is deciding what is the texture associated with the reward."},{"time":512268,"text":"The legends that you see in the movie don't appear for the monkey."},{"time":516100,"text":"And by the way, they don't read English anyway,"},{"time":518584,"text":"so they are here just for you to know that the correct target is shifting position."},{"time":523800,"text":"And yet, they can find them by tactile discrimination,"},{"time":527734,"text":"and they can press it and select it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530951,"text":"So when we look at the brains of these animals,"},{"time":533633,"text":"on the top panel you see the alignment of 125 cells"},{"time":537300,"text":"showing what happens with the brain activity, the electrical storms,"},{"time":541501,"text":"of this sample of neurons in the brain"},{"time":543568,"text":"when the animal is using a joystick."},{"time":545684,"text":"And that's a picture that every neurophysiologist knows."},{"time":548284,"text":"The basic alignment shows that these cells are coding for all possible directions."},{"time":553467,"text":"The bottom picture is what happens when the body stops moving"},{"time":559150,"text":"and the animal starts controlling either a robotic device or a computational avatar."},{"time":565284,"text":"As fast as we can reset our computers,"},{"time":568350,"text":"the brain activity shifts to start representing this new tool,"},{"time":574168,"text":"as if this too was a part of that primate's body."},{"time":579418,"text":"The brain is assimilating that too, as fast as we can measure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584133,"text":"So that suggests to us that our sense of self"},{"time":587751,"text":"does not end at the last layer of the epithelium of our bodies,"},{"time":591901,"text":"but it ends at the last layer of electrons of the tools that we're commanding with our brains."},{"time":597619,"text":"Our violins, our cars, our bicycles, our soccer balls, our clothing --"},{"time":602383,"text":"they all become assimilated by this voracious, amazing, dynamic system called the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609234,"text":"How far can we take it?"},{"time":610933,"text":"Well, in an experiment that we ran a few years ago, we took this to the limit."},{"time":615151,"text":"We had an animal running on a treadmill"},{"time":617633,"text":"at Duke University on the East Coast of the United States,"},{"time":619900,"text":"producing the brainstorms necessary to move."},{"time":622600,"text":"And we had a robotic device, a humanoid robot,"},{"time":626691,"text":"in Kyoto, Japan at ATR Laboratories"},{"time":629085,"text":"that was dreaming its entire life to be controlled by a brain,"},{"time":635179,"text":"a human brain, or a primate brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638452,"text":"What happens here is that the brain activity that generated the movements in the monkey"},{"time":643050,"text":"was transmitted to Japan and made this robot walk"},{"time":646517,"text":"while footage of this walking was sent back to Duke,"},{"time":650584,"text":"so that the monkey could see the legs of this robot walking in front of her."},{"time":655817,"text":"So she could be rewarded, not by what her body was doing"},{"time":659884,"text":"but for every correct step of the robot on the other side of the planet"},{"time":664845,"text":"controlled by her brain activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667454,"text":"Funny thing, that round trip around the globe took 20 milliseconds less"},{"time":674572,"text":"than it takes for that brainstorm to leave its head, the head of the monkey,"},{"time":678722,"text":"and reach its own muscle."},{"time":682592,"text":"The monkey was moving a robot that was six times bigger, across the planet."},{"time":688622,"text":"This is one of the experiments in which that robot was able to walk autonomously."},{"time":695022,"text":"This is CB1 fulfilling its dream in Japan"},{"time":700289,"text":"under the control of the brain activity of a primate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703989,"text":"So where are we taking all this?"},{"time":705978,"text":"What are we going to do with all this research,"},{"time":708321,"text":"besides studying the properties of this dynamic universe that we have between our ears?"},{"time":713989,"text":"Well the idea is to take all this knowledge and technology"},{"time":718822,"text":"and try to restore one of the most severe neurological problems that we have in the world."},{"time":724306,"text":"Millions of people have lost the ability to translate these brainstorms"},{"time":728889,"text":"into action, into movement."},{"time":731005,"text":"Although their brains continue to produce those storms and code for movements,"},{"time":736239,"text":"they cannot cross a barrier that was created by a lesion on the spinal cord."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741406,"text":"So our idea is to create a bypass,"},{"time":743856,"text":"is to use these brain-machine interfaces to read these signals,"},{"time":747888,"text":"larger-scale brainstorms that contain the desire to move again,"},{"time":751938,"text":"bypass the lesion using computational microengineering"},{"time":755907,"text":"and send it to a new body, a whole body called an exoskeleton,"},{"time":763021,"text":"a whole robotic suit that will become the new body of these patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768588,"text":"And you can see an image produced by this consortium."},{"time":772714,"text":"This is a nonprofit consortium called the Walk Again Project"},{"time":776773,"text":"that is putting together scientists from Europe,"},{"time":779556,"text":"from here in the United States, and in Brazil"},{"time":781421,"text":"together to work to actually get this new body built --"},{"time":785938,"text":"a body that we believe, through the same plastic mechanisms"},{"time":789272,"text":"that allow Aurora and other monkeys to use these tools through a brain-machine interface"},{"time":795074,"text":"and that allows us to incorporate the tools that we produce and use in our daily life."},{"time":800704,"text":"This same mechanism, we hope, will allow these patients,"},{"time":804388,"text":"not only to imagine again the movements that they want to make"},{"time":808156,"text":"and translate them into movements of this new body,"},{"time":811363,"text":"but for this body to be assimilated as the new body that the brain controls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818121,"text":"So I was told about 10 years ago"},{"time":821972,"text":"that this would never happen, that this was close to impossible."},{"time":827038,"text":"And I can only tell you that as a scientist,"},{"time":829489,"text":"I grew up in southern Brazil in the mid-'60s"},{"time":832475,"text":"watching a few crazy guys telling [us] that they would go to the Moon."},{"time":837523,"text":"And I was five years old,"},{"time":838984,"text":"and I never understood why NASA didn't hire Captain Kirk and Spock to do the job;"},{"time":843224,"text":"after all, they were very proficient --"},{"time":845656,"text":"but just seeing that as a kid"},{"time":849106,"text":"made me believe, as my grandmother used to tell me,"},{"time":852091,"text":"that \"impossible is just the possible"},{"time":853936,"text":"that someone has not put in enough effort to make it come true.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":857840,"text":"So they told me that it's impossible to make someone walk."},{"time":861639,"text":"I think I'm going to follow my grandmother's advice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864890,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866340,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}